      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HAYDEN'S GIFT (7) was strongly supported last start when a short priced favourite and duly saluted winning by 2.75 lengths at this track in a handy 19.44. Draws out wide but goes well at this distance. The form from his last run is stacking up nicely. In great recent form and expected to measure up again. BIZZARO BOY (2) comes off an average run last start when seventh at this track over 352m behind Federal Galaxy (20.70) in a Grade 5. Was a winner prior to that. Strong form has emerged from his last run. Has ability and can measure up. GOLDSTAR GRACE (1) finished in the minors last time but the start prior broke the clock when winning over 352m at this track, taking a Grade 5 in a blistering 19.54. Rates a leading chance if runs up to recent winning time. MARINA BAY (3) placed in slick time last start - worth some thought.",
